{"descriptions":[{"id":1269,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eGrammatical gender (masculine, feminine, neuter) does not exist in Tibetan.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eArticles, demonstratives, adjectives, and verbs are therefore invariable with respect to gender. Male and female sexes are, however, sometimes marked within the lexicon. This is accomplished by using distinct words, or else by means of suffixes (\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་\u003c/span\u003e or \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔོ་\u003c/span\u003e for the male and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e or \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམོ་\u003c/span\u003e for the female) in the case of certain pronouns and substantives that denote animate beings.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཡག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Yak\u0026rdquo; (male), \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའབྲི་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Yak-cow\u0026rdquo; (female) \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྟ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Horse\u0026rdquo; (generic), \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྒོད་མ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Mare\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Boy,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབུ་མོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Girl\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁམས་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Man from Kham,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁམས་མོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Woman from Kham\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྣལ་འབྱོར་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Yogin,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྣལ་འབྱོར་མ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Yoginī\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམཛོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Yak/cow hybrid,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམཛོ་མོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Female \u003cem\u003edzo\u003c/em\u003e\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNote that some pronouns make no distinction between \u0026ldquo;he\u0026rdquo; and \u0026ldquo;she\u0026rdquo;:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁོང་ཕྱུག་པོ་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;He/she is rich.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:23 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:23 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}